BENEDICT ARNOLD: A QUESTION OF HONOR
Monday, January 13 at 8pm / 7CT

He was one of America's greatest patriots, until love turned him into a traitor.
Join us for an A&E Original Movie starring Aiden Quinn and Kelsey Grammer 
that traces the events leading to the betrayal by one of the Continental Army's 
most decorated soldiers.

Before his very name became a synonym for "traitor," Benedict Arnold was 
not only George Washington's finest Revolutionary War officer, but one of his 
most trusted advisors and closest friends. How Arnold came to turn on his 
comrade, mentor and leader is a story as intriguing and commanding as the two 
legendary Generals themselves. 

LEARN MORE
Go behind-the-scenes, meet the cast and crew and enter our "Exile to England" 
Sweepstakes -- an England excursion Benedict Arnold would dream of, 
complete with everything - including a return ticket home!
Click here: http://chtah.com/a/tA$Hz-NADspiuALskE1ADy85AqP/bio4

